  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Veterinary Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>About Us</strong><br>\nWe are a full-service veterinary clinic in <strong>Sembawang</strong>, and we’re looking for talented, enthusiastic, and compassionate individuals to join our team. If you’re ready to take your career to the next level, we’d love to meet you!</p>\n<p><strong>Role &amp; Responsibilities</strong><br>\nAs a Veterinary Technician at our clinic, you will play a vital role in both patient care and clinic operations. Key responsibilities include:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Managing day-to-day reception and client communication</li>\n  <li>Assisting veterinarians with patient treatments and client enquiries</li>\n  <li>Monitoring anaesthesia and assisting during surgical procedures</li>\n  <li>Running laboratory tests and interpreting results</li>\n  <li>Providing treatments for hospitalised patients</li>\n  <li>Assisting with diagnostic imaging procedures</li>\n  <li>Performing ad-hoc administrative duties as required</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum of <strong>2 years’ relevant veterinary experience</strong></li>\n  <li>Strong technical and clinical skills</li>\n  <li>Ability to multi-task and work effectively in a team</li>\n  <li>Good communication skills and a compassionate attitude toward animals and clients</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>(Applicants with less experience may wish to apply for our Junior Veterinary Technician/Receptionist positions.)</em></p>\n<p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>A dynamic and supportive team environment</li>\n  <li>Opportunities to learn, grow, and advance your veterinary career</li>\n  <li>Hands-on experience with a wide range of procedures and cases</li>\n</ul>",
